# Documenting Zig

## Module scope
At the top of each file, use //! to state the module’s role, what it must not do (e.g. pure domain vs adapters), and how it fits the rest of the tree.

## Public API
Document every pub declaration with ///: types, const, struct fields, enum members, nested pub types, and pub const VTable function-pointer fields (treat each pointer as part of the public contract).

pub fn (and public methods)
For every public function, include:
- A one-line summary.
- /// Parameters: with a - \paramName`:` line per parameter (purpose, lifetime/borrowing if non-obvious).
- /// Returns: describing the success value, void, or the main error cases / propagated errors when that matters.

## Enums
Each enum member that is part of the public model gets its own /// (especially if names are constrained, e.g. avoiding Zig keywords).

## Private items
Non-pub helpers (vtable trampolines, small local functions, non-obvious fields): add a short // or /// line explaining why it exists or what invariant it preserves—no essays.

## Ownership / resources
When a caller must free, keep a slice valid, or not alias state, say so under Parameters or Returns.

## No doc drift
If the signature or behavior changes, update the comment in the same change.